<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10244720>
    dc:description "FIGURES 1–7. Details of the structure of the male of Stempellinella bazovae sp. nov. 1—head and antenna; 2—wing; 3–5— hypopygium; 6—superior volsella, dorsal view; 7—superior, median and inferior volsellae, dorsal view. Scale bar 20 µm (1–4), 50 µm (5–7)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10244720/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10244722>
    dc:description "FIGURES 8–16. Details of the structure of the male of Stempellinella chirka sp. nov. 8—head; 9—antenna; 10—wing; 11, 15—hypopygium, dorsal view; 12, 14—hypopygium, ventral view; 13—hypopygium, lateral view; 16—superior, median and inferior volsellae, dorsal view. Scale bar 20 µm (8–14), 50 µm (15–16)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10244722/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10244734>
    dc:description "FIGURES 35–40. Details of the structure of the male of Stempellinella coronata Inoue, Kawai et Imabayashi, 2004. 35—head and antenna; 36—wing; 37–38, 40—hypopygium; 39—superior and inferior volsellae, dorsal view. Scale bar 20 µm (35–38), 50 µm (39–40)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10244734/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

